HEADWORD: Desightment
<hw>De*sight"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
making unsightly; disfigurement.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To substitute jury masts at whatever <qex>desightment</qex> or
damage in risk.</q> <rj><qau>London Times.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Design</ent>⟦br⟧
